1 2. "Eligible Guard member" means a current member of the
2 Oklahoma National Guard in good standing who has a high school
3 diploma or who has completed General Educational Development (GED)
4 requirements and who has secured admission to and enrolled in an
5 Oklahoma educational institution;
6 3. "Graduate program" means a program offered by an Oklahoma
7 educational institution that leads to the award of a master's
8 degree;
9 4. "Program" means the Oklahoma National Guard Educational
10 Assistance Program established pursuant to the provisions of this
11 section; and
12 5. "Undergraduate program" means a program offered by an
13 Oklahoma educational institution that leads to the award of an
14 associate's degree or a baccalaureate degree.
15 C. There is hereby created the Oklahoma National Guard
16 Educational Assistance Program to provide assistance to eligible
17 Guard members who enroll in an Oklahoma educational institution.
18 Subject to the availability of funds, the amount of assistance shall
19 be equivalent to the amount of resident tuition, and approved
20 mandatory fees, program fees, and academic service fees, and any
21 other fees for courses in which the eligible Guard member is
22 enrolled, not to exceed a maximum of eighteen (18) credit hours each
23 semester. The amount of mandatory fees, program fees, academic
24 service fees, and any other fees shall be jointly reviewed and
