1 appr oved by the State Regents for Higher Education and the Military
2 Department of the State of Oklahoma before a determination to pay
3 the fees is made.
4 1. The amount of assistance provided to an eligible Guard
5 member enrolled in an undergraduate program shall not exceed a
6 maximum of one hundred twenty (120) credit hours in pursuit of an
7 associate's degree and/or a baccalaureate degree.
8 2. Subject to the assistance for eligible Guard members
9 enrolled in undergraduate programs being fully funded, assistance
10 shall be provided to an eligible Guard member with a baccalaureate
11 degree enrolled in a graduate program. The amount of assistance
12 provided to an eligible Guard member enrolled in a graduate program
13 shall not exceed a maximum of forty (40) credit hours in pursuit of
14 a master's degree.
15 3. Assistance provided pursuant to this section shall be
16 granted without any limitation other than the amount of funds
17 available for the Program and the number of eligible Guard members
18 who apply subject to any cap established by the Military Department.
19 4. Assistance allowed by this section shall not be allowed for
20 courses taken in excess of the requirements for completion of an
21 undergraduate program or a graduate program, whichever is applicable
22 for the eligible Guard member.
23 D. Assistance provided pursuant to this section shall be
24 allocated to the Oklahoma educational institution from the Oklahoma
