1 4. Maintain satisfactory participation in the Oklahoma National
2 Guard; and
3 5. Possess a Military Occupational Specialty (MOS) or Air Force
4 Specialty Code (AFSC) after his or her first semester.
5 G. An eligible Guard member seeking assistance pursuant to the
6 provisions of this section shall submit an application on a form
7 prescribed by the Military Department of the State of Oklahoma to
8 the Educational Service Office of the Military Department prior to
9 the semester for which assistance is sought. The Military
10 Department may establish a cap on the number of students per program
11 per semester to approve. The eligible Guard member's Commander or
12 his or her designee shall confirm a member's standing and
13 eligibility to the Oklahoma educational institution in which the
14 student is enrolled.
15 H. The eligible Guard member's Commander may deny an
16 application submitted by an eligible Guard member for continued
17 Program assistance if he or she fails to comply with the provisions
18 of paragraph 1, 2, or 3 of subsection F of this section.
19 I. An eligible Guard member who has received Program assistance
20 pursuant to the provisions of this section and who fails to comply
21 with the provisions of paragraph 4 of subsection F of this section
22 shall be required to repay an amount to be calculated as follows:
23 1. Determine the total amount of assistance provided pursuant
24 to the provisions of this section;
